+---
+name: cartridge
+description: "Use when the user wants a new educational cartridge created, asks for /cartridge, or needs the full manifest -> generator -> grading rules -> AI prompt workflow for a new cartridge."
+---
+
+# Cartridge
+
+Use this skill to create a new cartridge in dependency order so every generated file matches the same contract.
+
+## Required Inputs
+
+Ask the user for:
+
+- Subject
+- Topic
+- Mode count
+- Difficulty progression
+
+## Workflow
+
+### Step 1: `manifest.json`
+
+Define the contract first:
+
+- Modes
+- `inputFields`
+- Hints
+- Progression gates
+- Animation references
+
+This file defines the shape every later file must follow.
+
+### Step 2: `generator.js`
+
+Generate problems per mode and keep it aligned with `manifest.modes[].inputFields`.
+
+Include:
+
+- `generateProblem` logic for each mode
+- Shuffle-bag or equivalent anti-repetition logic
+- Template interpolation matching the manifest contract
+
+### Step 3: `grading-rules.js`
+
+Grade each field defined by the generator and manifest.
+
+Include:
+
+- `gradeField` logic per `fieldId`
+- `E`, `P`, and `I` scoring
+
+Field IDs must match `generator.js` exactly.
+
+### Step 4: `ai-grader-prompt.txt`
+
+Create placeholders that match the grading rules and generated fields exactly.
+
+## Finalization
+
+1. Register the new cartridge in `cartridges/registry.json`.
+2. Run `npm test` to check for regressions.
+3. Summarize what was created and any validation results.
+4. Ask whether the user wants to commit the new cartridge.
+
+## Guardrails
+
+- Do not start later files before the manifest contract is stable.
+- Keep names, field IDs, modes, and placeholders consistent across all four files.
+- Prefer the minimal complete cartridge over speculative extra features.
