+---
+name: lessonprep
+description: "Use when the user wants lesson materials prepared for a specific unit and lesson, especially transcripts, grading rubrics, live worksheets, or Blooket exports. Examples: /lessonprep, 'prepare Unit 6 Lesson 3', 'build the worksheet and Blooket for this lesson'."
+---
+
+# Lessonprep
+
+Use this skill to generate lesson assets in dependency order.
+
+If the user does not provide the lesson identifier, ask for it in the form `Unit N Lesson L`.
+
+## Workflow
+
+### Step 1: Transcript
+
+This step has no dependencies.
+
+- Check `apstats-live-worksheet/u{N}/` for existing transcripts.
+- If a transcript is missing, warn that Gemini is dormant and offer AI Studio or Whisper as the fallback path.
+
+### Step 2: Rubric
+
+This step depends on the transcript.
+
+- Check for `ai-grading-prompts-u{N}-l{L}.js`.
+- If missing, generate it from `curriculum_render/data/frameworks.js`.
+
+### Step 3: Worksheet
+
+This step depends on the transcript and rubric.
+
+- Check for `u{N}_lesson{L}_live.html`.
+- If missing, generate it using the live-worksheet skill or workflow.
+
+### Step 4: Blooket
+
+This step depends on the rubric and can run in parallel with Step 3 once the rubric exists.
+
+- Check for `u{N}_l{L}_blooket.csv`.
+- If missing, generate it using the blooket-quiz skill or workflow.
+
+### Step 5: Report
+
+- List what already existed.
+- List what was created.
+- Call out anything blocked by missing prerequisites.
+- Ask if the user wants to commit and push.
+
+## Guardrails
+
+- Do not generate downstream assets before their dependencies exist.
+- Reuse existing files when they are already present and valid.
+- Make the final report explicit about created versus pre-existing artifacts.
