+---
+name: analyze
+description: "Use when the user wants investigation only with no code changes, asks for /analyze, wants a root-cause analysis, code reading, design review, or structured findings without modifying files."
+---
+
+# Analyze
+
+This is analysis-only mode.
+
+## Rules
+
+- Do not edit files.
+- Do not run state-modifying commands.
+- Do not make commits, apply fixes, or change configuration.
+- Read source and inspect the current state only.
+
+## Workflow
+
+1. Read the relevant source files and supporting context.
+2. Investigate the question, bug, or design topic.
+3. Present structured findings with these sections:
+   - Summary
+   - Evidence with `file:line` references
+   - Options or recommendations
+   - Risks
+4. Stop after presenting findings and wait for the user to choose next steps.
+
+## Output Standard
+
+Keep the analysis grounded in evidence. If something is uncertain, label it as an inference and explain what would verify it.
